				\begin{document}$$_2$$\end{document} sequestration capacity (through deforestation) continued. Similarly, as diminishing conventional oil reserves are being supplemented with ‘unconventional oil’ from oil sands or tight oil resources, the increasing energy costs may become unsustainable. These and other substitutions skirt obvious natural resource limits in the short-run, but are subject to seemingly less obvious ecological limits in the long-run. Thus, the urgency to understand the relationship between economics, resources, and ecological systems might be more apparent to those outside the economics discipline.

